LGO 14
[normal]Submission from Mr &amp; Mrs G Thomas[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]I wish to 
[normal]submit written evidence to the select committee enquiry on the consequences of the local government Ombudsman giving incorrect information.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We have lived at the above address for 12 years and entry to our property is down a very narrow lane. The lane is 
[normal]part publicly maintained highway and part forestry track with a prescriptive rights-of-way.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In October 2011 our neighbour built a boundary wall which encroached onto the lane reducing the width by over 20% and now impedes the emergency services.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We inform
[normal]ed the authorities and a cessation of works was issued in the December
[normal] 2011
[normal]. After 7 months of inaction I was advised by my local authority to follow the Highways Act 1980. In October 2012  I phoned the Local Government Ombudsman for advice.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]I was advised 
[normal]to follow the complaints procedure through my local authority and if the issue was not resolved or I was not happy with the outcome then I could make an official complaint to the Ombudsman.
[normal]&#xa0;
