[normal]23-05-13. Supporting statement.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The above covered a period of over seven months and contains 51 A4 documents involving many 
[normal]departments incurring costs to the public purse and costs to myself.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The result of this complaints procedure was that my complaint was outside the Ombudsman’s adjudication.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]I would like to offer this evidence to the select committee review on the grounds 
[normal]that a large amount of money, both mine and the public’s, could have been saved if I had been given the correct advice on 17th October 2012.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]After experiencing the above, and the waste of time, energy and public money, I have come to the conclusion that 
[normal]if a member of the general public has a complaint against their local authority then there should be a mechanism in place to determine if the local government Ombudsman can investigate that complaint. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]By following the advice of the local authority I prev
[normal]ented the Local Government Ombudsman being able to investigate my case. In turn the Ombudsman advised me to follow a procedure that was outside his jurisdiction. He did not advise me of this loss of right or tell me about Fact Sheet G2 (which I finally rec
[normal]eived 30
[normal]th
[normal] April 2013, 6 months after I first approached the Ombudsman) before I started my complaints procedure.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]If the select committee require any supporting evidence to the above statement I will be more than happy to supply it.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]If the select committe
[normal]e would like me to give oral evidence I will also be more than happy to accommodate.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Listed below is all the documented evidence in date order.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]It ha
[normal]s now been over two years and this unlawful, wilful, obstruction of our Lane still remains. It seems I can do nothing about this and it has cost me £7500 to find this out because of incorrect advice from Government departments. Is this fair? 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Exclusive su[bold]mmary[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Report a crime - lose your home
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The Local Authority can give you information that will exclude the Local Government Ombudsman’s right to investigate your complaint and then the Ombudsman can do the same thing. This has resulted in my case, in me be
[normal]ing about to lose my home.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]16th November 2013
